      "comment": "PRESSURE POINT (2) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Finished in the minors last time when third (18.36) at this track making it back to back placings. Form here sound including two wins. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Well-placed to take this out. LEFEVRE RICO (1) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Chivas Lady (18.06) in a TG1-4W. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Leading player again. ROSE CHAMPAGNE (5) comes off an average effort last start when eighth at Warrnambool over 390m behind Paw Warringah (23.24) in a Bottom Up - Restricted Win. The form out of last race has been strong. In the mix. CADILLAC CLASS (7) must be included in main hopes on latest effort.",
